      "updated": 1772564890850,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Equation 1 Identifies the within-country–industry association between lagged robot\nintensity and labour input over time, controlling for observable and unobservable confounders.\n\nThe equaiton provides a baseline before testing institutional moderation\n\nB_1 : If robot intensity increases by 1 percent within a given country–industry, how does\nlabour input change?",
      "fontSize": 10.869578787974405,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Equation 1 Identifies the within-country–industry association between lagged robot intensity and labour input over time, controlling for observable and unobservable confounders.\n\nThe equaiton provides a baseline before testing institutional moderation\n\nB_1 : If robot intensity increases by 1 percent within a given country–industry, how does labour input change?",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
